HTML- Hypertext Markup Language (Buiding blocks)
----------------------------------------------BASIC HTML DOCUMENT:--------------------------------------------
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My first web page</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Heading</h1>
<p>Document content...</p>
</body>
</html>
---------------------------------------------------HTML TAGS:-------------------------------------------------
<!DOCTYPE html> = This tag defines the document type and HTML version
<html> = Root tag and this tag encloses the complete HTML document
<head> = Heading (no content), here we can link titles, keywords(which are not visible)
<body> = This tag represents the document's body or content part which is visible
<h> = Heading tag-<h1>,<h2>,<h3>,<h4>,<h5> and <h6>
<p> = Paragraph tag
<br/> = Line break tag and the content will be placed between the 'br' and forward slash
<center> = This tag to put any content in the center of the page or any table cell
<hr /> = This tag is to introduce a horizontal line in the content and no need of a closing tag
<pre> = This tag is text to follow the exact format of how it is written in the HTML document
&nbsp; = This tag helps to avoid breaking the text
<img> = Image tag
<i> = Italic tag
<sup> = Superscript tag: h<sub>2</sub>O
<sub> = Subscript tag
<small>hello</small> = For smaller font
<b> = Bold tag
<u> = Underline tag
<s> = Strike off tag
<body bg color="red"> = For changing the background colour
<tt> = Monospaced tag
<big> = For larger font
